{"type":"message","id":"58d407d4","parentId":"5d0fcf92","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:30:02.811Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.process:10","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- mcp-grep (5 tools, 23.9s)\n- filesystem (14 tools, 25.3s)\n✔ Listed 8 servers (7 healthy; 1 offline).\n\nProcess still running."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"warm-trail","aggregated":"mcporter 0.7.3 — Listing 8 server(s) (per-server timeout: 30s)\n- dashscope_websearch (1 tool, 0.4s)\n- ddgs_search (1 tool, 1.4s)\n[mcporter] Restarting 'playwright' before retrying listTools: MCP error -32000: Connection closed\n- image-recognition (1 tool, 9.6s)\n- playwright (offline — unable to reach server, 9.7s)\n- ddgsearch (3 tools, 12.3s)\n- paddleocr-mcp (1 tool, 16.7s)\n- mcp-grep (5 tools, 23.9s)\n- filesystem (14 tools, 25.3s)\n✔ Listed 8 servers (7 healthy; 1 offline).\n","name":"mcporter list","retryInMs":5000},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772249402806}}
{"type":"message","id":"28170fdc","parentId":"58d407d4","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:30:11.443Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"看了下现有的MCP，没有专门的workflow/pipeline工具。\n\n**实话实说：**\n\n我搜了一圈，没找到现成的\"pipeline MCP\"。这玩意儿要么太新没人做，要么大家直接用代码写了不用MCP封装。\n\n**两个方案：**\n\n1. **用现有工具拼** —— filesystem + SQLite + 定时脚本，我自己写逻辑\n2. **造一个新的** —— 但得你同意，而且我得先想清楚接口设计\n\n我倾向方案1，先跑起来再说。用Python写个简单的pipeline脚本，调用filesystem存数据，用我（千问）做分析，Telegram Bot做对话通道。\n\n你要我直接开干吗？还是先看看有没有别的现成方案？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":24479,"output":149,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24628,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772249402812}}
{"type":"message","id":"02a64531","parentId":"28170fdc","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:30:25.700Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-02-28 11:30 GMT+8] 你的搜索时阿里那个，哥，你怎么还在用kimi啊"}],"timestamp":1772249425695}}
{"type":"message","id":"71381cf7","parentId":"02a64531","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:30:29.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"我操，又tm犯蠢了。\n\n你说得对，TOOLS.md里写得明明白白——**dashscope_websearch是首选**，国内最快最稳。我脑子抽了去用kimi。\n\n让我重新搜："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:10","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mcporter call dashscope_websearch.bailian_web_search query=\"MCP pipeline workflow automation server\" count=5","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":24417,"output":90,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24507,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772249425699}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc035a68","parentId":"71381cf7","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:30:34.594Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.exec:10","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"pages\": [\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Let your AI work with real data, without the risk MCP Server Now Available! Let developers, analysts, and data engineers ship faster—AI handles the heavy lifting, Keboola keeps it reliable and secure. Works with What Keboola MCP Server Unlocks Build with AI Turn natural language into governed transformations and pipelines. Ship to Production faster Run from quick prototypes to production without re-engineering. Always in Control Full observability, audit, and governance baked into every workflow. See It in Action Create Pipelines Debug Jobs Generate Documentation Data Quality Assessment Describe a workflow, get a pipeline Stop wiring connectors by hand. In Cursor, describe the pipeline and Keboola makes it governed and production - ready. From ingestion to transformation, you go from idea to running pipeline in minutes. #1 Create your Project Login or Set up your Keboola. #2 Connect with MCP Connect to your AI Assistant or IDE. #3 Data-Vibe your Pipeline Sleep through the night. MCP Server Introduction Thanks to our MCP Server, our clients can operate Keboola up to 10X faster - unlocking new levels of efficiency and control. You’re in good company \\\"We can go from a full POC to delivery in a third of the time while delivering key initiatives for our clients across AI, Automation and agentic work to accelerate these ever more prevalent use cases for our customers. Keboola MCP makes this even easier than ever .\\\" Daniel Haville, BI:PROCSI  \\\"Great job, team, on your server. For us at Apify, it was the perfect use case —simplifying data extraction from multiple Apify Actors in Keboola and then building SQL transformations directly in a Flow. What I thought would be manual or technically inaccessible, Claude, via MCP, built it for me automatically. It's a true door opener to creating amazing transformations with complex data sets, even for non-technical users.\\\" Sameh Jarour, Apify \\\"following the readme, Claude was all set within 10 mins. According to me this is a wild thing !\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"\",\n      \"title\": \"MCP Server — AI-Powered Pipeline Development | Keboola\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.keboola.com/product/mcp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Trigger onuploadto a specific folder. Analyzedimensions (flag low-res). Transformto a 960px web-ready variant. Use anLLMto generate alt text. Write metadata(description). Movethe original to an approved folder. Notifya human via email. Logeverything for observability. You’ll scaffold the flow from your editor via the MCP server (fast path), then enable and test it in the MediaFlows UI. Who’s This For? Copy link to this heading Devs who want a reproducible visual media pipeline with minimal glue code. Teams exploring AI-assisted workflows (alt text, captions, summarization). Anyone who prefers building from their editor but deploying with UI controls and logs. What You’ll Need Copy link to this heading A Cloudinary account withMediaFlowsenabled (pick a target product environment). Cloud name, API key, API secretfor that environment. Windsurf(or Cursor) with MCP support. Two folders in your Cloudinary environment:incoming/andproducts/approved/. (Optional) A structured metadata text field nameddescription\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"\",\n      \"title\": \"Automate End-to-End Image Workflows With Cloudinary MediaFlows and MCP\",\n      \"url\": \"https://cloudinary.com/blog/media-workflow-automation-mediaflows-cloudinary-mcp-server-windsurf\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Workflow Server 运行在设计器中创建的流程的实例。在开发环境中,回放服务器使您能够在构建过程时运行这些过程。 当您准备就绪时,可以在测试和生产环境中的 Workflow Server 上安装和运行这些相同的流程。 由于 Workflow Server 起着如此重要的作用,因此您应该监视其性能,并确保在安装和运行流程的测试或生产版本时完成所有必需的设置和配置。 以下部分说明如何访问 Process Admin Console 来执行管理任务,同时还提供可通过指向详细信息和过程的链接来执行的任务类型的列表。 Process Admin Console 使您能够在运行时环境 (开发,测试,登台和生产) 以及回放服务器中管理 Workflow Server。\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"https://www.ibm.com/content/dam/adobe-cms/default-images/icon-512x512.png\",\n      \"title\": \"管理Workflow Server\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ibm.com/docs/zh/cloud-paks/cp-biz-automation/23.0.1?topic=administering-managing-workflow-servers\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"如果你还没看过关于 MCP 的技术深度解析,这里快速过一遍:MCP 是一套开放标准,核心思路就是把”智能”(LLM)和”能力”(工具)解耦开来。 老路子:到处写胶水代码 没有MCP 之前,想让 AI 连个 Postgres 数据库,你得自己写 API 封装、手动定义 schema、处理认证,每次模型提供商改了 tool-calling 语法还得跟着改代码。这是维护噩梦,而且把你锁死在某个供应商上。 MCP 的做法:通用适配器 MCP 提供了一个通用接口。你部署一个”Postgres MCP Server”,然后 Claude Code、Cursor、Fusion 或者任何兼容 MCP 的客户端都能直接跟它通信。 这种标准化让整个生态从”实验性脚本”进化到了”生产级基础设施”。下面列出的这些 MCP Server,都是能在生产环境跑的工具,给你的 AI 代理提供了对真实世界的结构化访问能力。 MCP 安全须知 把MCP Server 接到你的文件、数据库甚至 Stripe 账户上,本质上更像是在接入一个微服务,而不是装个 npm 包那么简单。几个基本原则: 先从只读服务开始(文档、搜索、监控) 控制每个 Server 的影响范围(按项目分 Key、限定目录、用开发/测试数据) 记录调用日志,这样你能看到 AI 到底在怎么用你的工具 文章最后会再详细聊安全最佳实践。\",\n      \"hostname\": \"知乎\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"https://ss1.baidu.com/6ONXsjip0QIZ8tyhnq/it/u=493147230,3096476255&fm=195&app=88&f=JPEG?w=200&h=200\",\n      \"title\": \"2026 年开发者最值得装的 MCP Server 完全指南\",\n      \"url\": \"https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/2010143969758188866\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Containers:  The following tables list the configurable parameters and their default values. All properties are mandatory, unless they have a default value or are explicitly optional. Although IBM® Business Automation Workflow might seem to install correctly when some parameters are omitted, this kind of configuration is not supported. Shared configuration parameters Some configuration parameters can be shared by an installation of multiple automation components.  A pattern includes all the components that are needed to accomplish a specific set of cross-component functional tasks. The scripts and custom resource templates that are provided for the patterns reduce the number of steps you need to do to prepare your environment. The following table shows shared configuration parameters for patterns and dynamic storage.\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"https://www.ibm.com/content/dam/adobe-cms/default-images/icon-512x512.png\",\n      \"title\": \"IBM Business Automation Workflow Server parameters\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/baw/20.0.0?topic=workflow-business-automation-server-parameters\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"request_id\": \"f7a04d7c-ee4b-41cb-9fca-2762c89f0353\",\n  \"tools\": [],\n  \"status\": 0\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4787,"aggregated":"{\n  \"pages\": [\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Let your AI work with real data, without the risk MCP Server Now Available! Let developers, analysts, and data engineers ship faster—AI handles the heavy lifting, Keboola keeps it reliable and secure. Works with What Keboola MCP Server Unlocks Build with AI Turn natural language into governed transformations and pipelines. Ship to Production faster Run from quick prototypes to production without re-engineering. Always in Control Full observability, audit, and governance baked into every workflow. See It in Action Create Pipelines Debug Jobs Generate Documentation Data Quality Assessment Describe a workflow, get a pipeline Stop wiring connectors by hand. In Cursor, describe the pipeline and Keboola makes it governed and production - ready. From ingestion to transformation, you go from idea to running pipeline in minutes. #1 Create your Project Login or Set up your Keboola. #2 Connect with MCP Connect to your AI Assistant or IDE. #3 Data-Vibe your Pipeline Sleep through the night. MCP Server Introduction Thanks to our MCP Server, our clients can operate Keboola up to 10X faster - unlocking new levels of efficiency and control. You’re in good company \\\"We can go from a full POC to delivery in a third of the time while delivering key initiatives for our clients across AI, Automation and agentic work to accelerate these ever more prevalent use cases for our customers. Keboola MCP makes this even easier than ever .\\\" Daniel Haville, BI:PROCSI  \\\"Great job, team, on your server. For us at Apify, it was the perfect use case —simplifying data extraction from multiple Apify Actors in Keboola and then building SQL transformations directly in a Flow. What I thought would be manual or technically inaccessible, Claude, via MCP, built it for me automatically. It's a true door opener to creating amazing transformations with complex data sets, even for non-technical users.\\\" Sameh Jarour, Apify \\\"following the readme, Claude was all set within 10 mins. According to me this is a wild thing !\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"\",\n      \"title\": \"MCP Server — AI-Powered Pipeline Development | Keboola\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.keboola.com/product/mcp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Trigger onuploadto a specific folder. Analyzedimensions (flag low-res). Transformto a 960px web-ready variant. Use anLLMto generate alt text. Write metadata(description). Movethe original to an approved folder. Notifya human via email. Logeverything for observability. You’ll scaffold the flow from your editor via the MCP server (fast path), then enable and test it in the MediaFlows UI. Who’s This For? Copy link to this heading Devs who want a reproducible visual media pipeline with minimal glue code. Teams exploring AI-assisted workflows (alt text, captions, summarization). Anyone who prefers building from their editor but deploying with UI controls and logs. What You’ll Need Copy link to this heading A Cloudinary account withMediaFlowsenabled (pick a target product environment). Cloud name, API key, API secretfor that environment. Windsurf(or Cursor) with MCP support. Two folders in your Cloudinary environment:incoming/andproducts/approved/. (Optional) A structured metadata text field nameddescription\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"\",\n      \"title\": \"Automate End-to-End Image Workflows With Cloudinary MediaFlows and MCP\",\n      \"url\": \"https://cloudinary.com/blog/media-workflow-automation-mediaflows-cloudinary-mcp-server-windsurf\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Workflow Server 运行在设计器中创建的流程的实例。在开发环境中,回放服务器使您能够在构建过程时运行这些过程。 当您准备就绪时,可以在测试和生产环境中的 Workflow Server 上安装和运行这些相同的流程。 由于 Workflow Server 起着如此重要的作用,因此您应该监视其性能,并确保在安装和运行流程的测试或生产版本时完成所有必需的设置和配置。 以下部分说明如何访问 Process Admin Console 来执行管理任务,同时还提供可通过指向详细信息和过程的链接来执行的任务类型的列表。 Process Admin Console 使您能够在运行时环境 (开发,测试,登台和生产) 以及回放服务器中管理 Workflow Server。\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"https://www.ibm.com/content/dam/adobe-cms/default-images/icon-512x512.png\",\n      \"title\": \"管理Workflow Server\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ibm.com/docs/zh/cloud-paks/cp-biz-automation/23.0.1?topic=administering-managing-workflow-servers\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"如果你还没看过关于 MCP 的技术深度解析,这里快速过一遍:MCP 是一套开放标准,核心思路就是把”智能”(LLM)和”能力”(工具)解耦开来。 老路子:到处写胶水代码 没有MCP 之前,想让 AI 连个 Postgres 数据库,你得自己写 API 封装、手动定义 schema、处理认证,每次模型提供商改了 tool-calling 语法还得跟着改代码。这是维护噩梦,而且把你锁死在某个供应商上。 MCP 的做法:通用适配器 MCP 提供了一个通用接口。你部署一个”Postgres MCP Server”,然后 Claude Code、Cursor、Fusion 或者任何兼容 MCP 的客户端都能直接跟它通信。 这种标准化让整个生态从”实验性脚本”进化到了”生产级基础设施”。下面列出的这些 MCP Server,都是能在生产环境跑的工具,给你的 AI 代理提供了对真实世界的结构化访问能力。 MCP 安全须知 把MCP Server 接到你的文件、数据库甚至 Stripe 账户上,本质上更像是在接入一个微服务,而不是装个 npm 包那么简单。几个基本原则: 先从只读服务开始(文档、搜索、监控) 控制每个 Server 的影响范围(按项目分 Key、限定目录、用开发/测试数据) 记录调用日志,这样你能看到 AI 到底在怎么用你的工具 文章最后会再详细聊安全最佳实践。\",\n      \"hostname\": \"知乎\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"https://ss1.baidu.com/6ONXsjip0QIZ8tyhnq/it/u=493147230,3096476255&fm=195&app=88&f=JPEG?w=200&h=200\",\n      \"title\": \"2026 年开发者最值得装的 MCP Server 完全指南\",\n      \"url\": \"https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/2010143969758188866\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"snippet\": \"Containers:  The following tables list the configurable parameters and their default values. All properties are mandatory, unless they have a default value or are explicitly optional. Although IBM® Business Automation Workflow might seem to install correctly when some parameters are omitted, this kind of configuration is not supported. Shared configuration parameters Some configuration parameters can be shared by an installation of multiple automation components.  A pattern includes all the components that are needed to accomplish a specific set of cross-component functional tasks. The scripts and custom resource templates that are provided for the patterns reduce the number of steps you need to do to prepare your environment. The following table shows shared configuration parameters for patterns and dynamic storage.\",\n      \"hostname\": \"无\",\n      \"hostlogo\": \"https://www.ibm.com/content/dam/adobe-cms/default-images/icon-512x512.png\",\n      \"title\": \"IBM Business Automation Workflow Server parameters\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/baw/20.0.0?topic=workflow-business-automation-server-parameters\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"request_id\": \"f7a04d7c-ee4b-41cb-9fca-2762c89f0353\",\n  \"tools\": [],\n  \"status\": 0\n}","cwd":"D:\\.openclaw\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772249434590}}
